Class Fruits

java.lang.Object
com.example.projectfx.resources.Resource
com.example.projectfx.resources.Fruits
All Implemented Interfaces:
Consumable
public class Fruits extends Resource
Represents fruits as a resource in the ecosystem. Fruits have a ripening rate and can regenerate based on that rate. They can also be consumed by species.

      public void regenerate()
      Regenerates fruits based on their ripening rate. The quantity of fruits is increased by a calculated amount based on the ripening rate.
      Specified by:

    • consume

    • isConsumed

      public boolean isConsumed()
      Determines whether the fruits have been consumed. Since fruits can be consumed over time, this method checks if the fruits are still available.
      Returns:
      false because fruits are not fully consumed after one action.
